## Critical Rules for Code Changes

### ALWAYS Before Committing
1. ✅ **Tests pass**: `npm run test:run` shows 34/34 green
2. ✅ **Lint clean**: `npm run lint` reports no errors  
3. ✅ **Build succeeds**: `npm run check` completes successfully
4. ✅ **Types current**: `npm run cf-typegen` if Cloudflare changes made

### NEVER Do This
- ❌ Use `any` types (ESLint will catch this)
- ❌ Commit failing tests
- ❌ Modify D1 schema without updating both interfaces
- ❌ Skip webhook signature verification
- ❌ Allow direct-to-map posting (bypass moderation)

### Data Integrity Rules
- 🔒 **Only approved pins in D1**: Webhook enforces this rule
- 🔒 **Webhook is source of truth**: For Sanity → D1 sync
- 🔒 **All proposals start pending**: No exceptions
- 🔒 **IP always logged**: For spam prevention

This rule serves as the definitive reference for the complete "Bucureștiul Posibil" system. Consult before making changes to ensure consistency and system integrity.